##

EXAMPLE: tests/huge_number.stult

This test exercises Stult's large-number behaviour.

Whole-number parts should be able to grow beyond fixed integer or
floating-point precision limits, while decimal parts remain bounded
by the language's maximum decimal scale.

##

ASSERT : STD["ASSERT"]

HUGE : 

ASSERT["TRUE"](HUGE + 1 > HUGE, "huge integer should increase when one is added")
ASSERT["TRUE"](HUGE * 2 > HUGE, "huge integer should increase when doubled")
ASSERT["TRUE"](HUGE - 1 < HUGE, "huge integer should decrease when one is subtracted")

DECIMAL : HUGE + 0.25

ASSERT["TRUE"](DECIMAL > HUGE, "huge decimal should be greater than its whole-number part")
ASSERT["TRUE"](DECIMAL < HUGE + 1, "huge decimal should remain below the next whole number")
